Probably the most underrated pizza spot in Chicago. You'd miss it if you walked past it - connected to the Best Western across from the giant McDonald's on Ohio St. - but the quality of the ingredients, the customer service, the freshness, it's tough to beat. It's also not too expensive and it's ready quickly. Delivery guy was super friendly and accommodating, brought us plates and napkins upon request, and thanked us for our business. It was just a really pleasant experience and has become a go-to spot for me. Highly recommend trying it out!

I have had Lou Malnatis, Giordano's, Uno, and Gino's. Ora beats them all. I think what sets them apart is the sauce it's so fresh and flavorful. The dough is always perfectly cooked, and the cheese and toppings are delicious. The staff is always very friendly and attentive.

Simply said top 3 best pizza in Chicago. It's in the sauce guys. Anyone can get fresh mozz and dough ingredients. the sauce is the bomb. Too many Chicago places have changed towards more tomato. Fine...but have to season it still. Very well done here for a long time . Great job!

We asked around town for recommendations for a great Chicago style deep dish pizza. Everyone said Giordano’s and Malnati’s. Don’t listen to that advice. Pizzeria Ora is by far, hands down, THE BEST! The owner, Walid, is the most genuinely nice person. You can tell he really takes pride in what he has created with Pizzeria Ora. As he should. Our server, Paco, was awesome. Attentive, friendly, and generous. I would recommend this place over any of the big chains any day of the week. We ordered two deep dish 6” pizzas and a 9” thin crust. All were amazing.

The experience at this restaurant was amazing. I was part of a group of 11. We were there every night but I want to highlight one particular night. It was the fullest it was ever during my time here and there was only one waitress for the whole place. Her name is Kim and I watched as she bounced from table to table to telephone to keypad and back again. What astonished me is she kept her smile and she remained so pleasant and never complained. This is what customer service is. The mark of a successful business is it being busy. But when it happens, it's the employees that have to deal with the hard part of that. But even in that, there are still the same expectations. Kim showed that. It was obvious that she, like any human would be, was exhausted but you wouldn't know unless you watched the moments she stopped to take a breath before getting back into the cycle. Kim was amazing and I made sure she knew that! Thank you Kim!

I took my kids to Chicago over Memorial weekend to see the sights and enjoy the tastes of the Windy City. We walked from our hotel about 8 blocks to go to Gino's East side to enjoy a true Chicago Deep Dish pie...but they were closed. So my daughter looked up pizza places near us and we found Pizzeria Ora just 2 blocks away, and decided to give them a try as they had 4.2 stars out of 5 on reviews! Well the minute we walked in we were greeted by our waitres Kim, who was AWESOME, friendly, great service, and funny to boot! We asked what was good for appetizer and she suggested their nachos while we waited and we ordered a large pepperoni and sausage with onions and green peppers and mushroom deep dish pizza! Oh my Lord, it was the BEST deep dish ever and even beat Gino's East side in my opinion! We give Pizzeria Ora a perfect 10! As well as our waitress Kim a perfect 10 as she made it a perfect experience! Thanks Kim and Pizzeria Ora!!! We will be back! I highly recommend everyone to give the deep dish a try! You won't be sorry!! Sincerely, Robert Rosengren

Great Pizza. Had eight slices, couldn't walk for a few days. Zero regrets.

first the people here are great. we stayed at the hotel connected to the pizzeria and so we had breakfast there two. we have had the Blanco Pizza, the Marina seafood pizza and the supreme.. they are all great!

Not a bad place for deep dish and certainly good as a plan b to the other more touristy options. Beer options aren't anything to write home about. Good service, no frills tasty pizza in a modest setting.

Just spent 4 days in Chicago and stayed across the street at the Ohio House. Pizzeria Ora was are go to breakfast place in the morning. Can only say that the service there is great the breakfast was great and really enjoyed going there every morning.
Very ordinary.  Not bad, but quite unremarkable.

In search for deep dish pizza me and my girlfriend ended up here. A quiet place, since there were almost no guests this night. In the background, a TV screen with ESPN. Many available tables, very few guests. Personally I liked it, as we both were kind of tired after a day swimming at Indiana Dunes. Anyways, we ordered our food and drinks: 30 bucks for a medium pizza, a bottle of goose island IPA and a root beer. The food was simply delicious, and the service impeccable. The only thing I can think of that was not A+ was the crust of the pizza, which needed a little more salt/taste. But when you visit, you can probably ask them to salt it up a little. Also, we loved the root beer so much we had to ask our waitress where we could buy it (we're Norwegian tourists visiting Chicago (and the US) for the first time, so we like to ask, not look for ourselves :p) and she told us basically at any grocery store (what a bombshell). Then, just as we were leaving, the waitress came up to us with two bottles of root beer, telling us it's on the house. Made our day! Recommended. Food 9/10 (because of the missing salt), Service 10/10

The wait at Lou Malnati's was 90 minutes for a party of two...no thanks. Walked a couple blocks and found this place. It doesn't have a "wow" factor when you walk in, but the deep dish was still great, the service was good and the prices were reasonable.
Great food and the bartender was very good.   Definitely recommend
Very good Chicago style deep dish. Definitely have a unique flavor to the marinara sauce. Drink special were great as well as the appetizers.
Don't listen to the negative reviews! Honestly a great thin crust pizza. Great value & awesome pizza!
Their pizza is delicious! Lots of flavor. The service is great.

Wanted to try authentic deep dish pizza while visiting Chicago. After searching different places we decided on Pizzera Ora based on the reviews. Let me just say we were not let down. The deep dish pizza was fantastic! They do let you know up front the deep dish pizza takes 40 minutes, but it was cooked to perfection. We loved the small, casual and laid back atmosphere of the restaurant. It will be on our list the next time we are in the city.

Definitely liked this place. I had never been to one of the non-chain deep dish places in Chicago. Although not as good as my favorite Lou Malnati's, it was quite good. The crust is delicious and has a slightly crunchy but not too crunchy texture. Definitely give this place a shot.
do they make better pizza?
Better than Uno's deep dish pizza. No line or wait to be seated... Awesome prices and great service too!
Great hotel bar restaurant.Great value in breakfast. We always stop here when we stay a t the Best Western River North Hotel.
We go here every February with our High School Model UN group.  They treat us like kings. Food is great, service is awesome, and the owner is a great guy!  Can't wait until this February trip!
